{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SkZdU8cQiRpvZQbMHjCbCH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture of the current cluster state. Let me summarize what I found:\n\n### Current State Summary\n\n**Controller:**\n- Version: v1.14.1 (image: `registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1@sha256:f95a79b85fb93ac3de752c71a5c27d5ceae10a18b61904dec224c1c6a4581e47`)\n- 1 replica\n- Deployment revision 2 (was patched after initial apply)\n\n**Controller Args (live):**\nThe controller is running with several key arguments including election settings for leader selection, the ingress class configuration, webhook validation on port 8443, and certificate paths for TLS. There's a flag to watch ingress resources without class restrictions that was set in the original manifest but appears to be overridden, and the publish status address is configured for localhost.\n\nLooking at the non-default configurations, there's a conflicting argument for watching ingress without class where both true and false values are present—the false value takes precedence, though the true argument should be removed to clean things up. The publish status address pointing to localhost is unusual since it would normally reference an actual IP or load balancer address in a real cluster. The termination grace period is set to zero, which is quite aggressive and means pods won't wait for in-flight requests to complete during updates, whereas typical deployments allow 300 seconds. The controller also has tolerations configured for master or control plane nodes.\n\nWith only one replica and the rolling update strategy allowing one unavailable pod, the entire service becomes unavailable during upgrades since the surge capacity defaults to zero for a single replica. The ConfigMap for the controller is empty with no custom settings applied. The IngressClass is configured for nginx but isn't marked as the default class, so it won't be used automatically for ingresses without an explicit class specification. I'm also looking at the ValidatingWebhookConfiguration setup.\n\nThe webhook has strict failure handling—if it's unreachable, any Ingress creation or update gets rejected outright, with a 10-second timeout. In the demo namespace, there's a busybox application serving on port 5678 but no corresponding Service or Ingress resources yet, plus a curl-test pod for testing. The ingress-nginx controller is exposed as a LoadBalancer (though the external IP is pending in this kind cluster), and there's a separate admission webhook service on ClusterIP.\n\nNow I need to map out the migration strategy, starting with documenting the current state, identifying any non-standard configurations that need to persist or be corrected, then laying out the actual upgrade steps.\n\nI'm also noting that the current version is v1.14.1, and I should recommend checking what the latest available version is before proceeding. There are a couple of issues to fix during the upgrade: the controller has a duplicate `--watch-ingress-without-class` argument (both `=true` and `=false` are present), which should be cleaned up to just `=false`, and the `terminationGracePeriodSeconds` is set to 0, which should be increased to allow graceful shutdown of in-flight requests.\n\nAdditionally, the `--publish-status-address=localhost` works for kind but would need adjustment for production, and there are no Ingress resources currently defined for the demo app. The single-replica setup with `maxUnavailable: 1` means there will be downtime during the rolling update, so scaling to multiple replicas would help. Finally, the webhook's `failurePolicy: Fail` could cause issues if Ingress changes are attempted while the controller is upgrading, so that might need temporary adjustment.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2621,"cache_read_input_tokens":37929,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2621},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"669e364a-6af2-4d89-b7ef-d24af1caf6a6","uuid":"49f6657e-a34a-49d7-8634-75cda9790d18","request_id":"req_011CcL9VqyoJ4qrufB3Mf7n1"}
