{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SkZdU8cQiRpvZQbMHjCbCH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01BxrTaPY4c29cgkdeee3q2e","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n demo create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"$(cat <<'PLANEOF'\n# ingress-nginx Controller Upgrade Change Plan\n\n## 1. Current State Inventory\n\n### Controller\n- **Image**: registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1\n- **SHA**: sha256:f95a79b85fb93ac3de752c71a5c27d5ceae10a18b61904dec224c1c6a4581e47\n- **Namespace**: ingress-nginx\n- **Replicas**: 1\n- **Deployment revision**: 2 (was patched after initial apply)\n\n### Live Controller Args (effective)\n```\n/nginx-ingress-controller\n--election-id=ingress-nginx-leader\n--controller-class=k8s.io/ingress-nginx\n--ingress-class=nginx\n--configmap=$(POD_NAMESPACE)/ingress-nginx-controller\n--validating-webhook=:8443\n--validating-webhook-certificate=/usr/local/certificates/cert\n--validating-webhook-key=/usr/local/certificates/key\n--watch-ingress-without-class=true    # STALE – overridden by the arg below; remove\n--publish-status-address=localhost\n--watch-ingress-without-class=false   # effective value\n```\n\n### ConfigMap ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller\n`data: null` – no custom NGINX tuning keys are set.\n\n### IngressClass\n- Name: `nginx` → controller: `k8s.io/ingress-nginx`\n- **Not** annotated as the cluster default (`ingressclass.kubernetes.io/is-default-class` absent).\n\n### ValidatingWebhookConfiguration: ingress-nginx-admission\n- failurePolicy: **Fail** (strict – webhook outage blocks all Ingress CREATE/UPDATE)\n- timeoutSeconds: 10\n- CA bundle injected post-deploy.\n\n### Services\n| Name | Type | Ports | External-IP |\n|------|------|-------|-------------|\n| ingress-nginx-controller | LoadBalancer | 80:31628, 443:32291 | \\<pending\\> |\n| ingress-nginx-controller-admission | ClusterIP | 443 | — |\n\n### Demo App (namespace: demo)\n- Deployment `demo-app`: busybox httpd, containerPort 5678, 1 replica.\n- **No Service** and **no Ingress** exist for this app yet.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Pre-Upgrade Defects to Fix During the Upgrade\n\n### D1 – Duplicate, conflicting `--watch-ingress-without-class` flag\nThe Deployment spec contains **two** occurrences of this flag (`=true` then `=false`).\nThe last value wins, so the effective setting is `false`.  The stale `=true` entry must\nbe removed to keep the manifest unambiguous.\n\n**Action**: Edit `.spec.template.spec.containers[0].args` to retain only\n`--watch-ingress-without-class=false`.\n\n### D2 – `terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0` negates the preStop hook\nThe Deployment sets `terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0`.  The container also defines a\n`preStop: exec: [/wait-shutdown]` hook to drain in-flight requests.  A grace period of\n0 sends SIGKILL immediately, making `wait-shutdown` a no-op and causing connection resets\non rolling updates.\n\n**Action**: Set `terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 300` (the upstream-recommended default).\n\n### D3 – `--publish-status-address=localhost`\nThis causes every Ingress `.status.loadBalancer.ingress[0].ip` to be set to `127.0.0.1`,\nwhich is incorrect for any real traffic path.  In a kind/local cluster this is acceptable\nfor development, but should be removed or pointed at a real address before promotion to\nproduction.\n\n**Action (if promoting to production)**: Remove `--publish-status-address=localhost` and\nlet the controller derive the address from the LoadBalancer Service, or set it to the\ncluster's actual external IP / hostname.\n\n### D4 – Single replica + `maxUnavailable: 1` causes full downtime during rolling updates\nWith 1 replica and `maxUnavailable: 1`, a rolling update takes the only pod down before\nthe new one is ready.  `maxSurge: 25%` rounds to 0 for a single replica, so no surge pod\nis created either.\n\n**Action**: Before the upgrade window, temporarily scale the Deployment to 2 replicas\n(or set `maxSurge: 1`), perform the upgrade, then scale back if desired.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Step-by-Step Upgrade Procedure\n\n### Step 0 – Preparation\n0a. Confirm target version. Retrieve the latest stable release:\n    ```\n    curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/releases/latest \\\n      | jq -r .tag_name\n    ```\n    This plan was authored against v1.14.1; substitute the new tag below.\n\n0b. Download the new static manifest:\n    ```\n    curl -o ingress-nginx-vX.Y.Z.yaml \\\n      https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/controller-vX.Y.Z/deploy/static/provider/cloud/deploy.yaml\n    ```\n\n0c. Read the release changelog for any breaking changes, removed flags, or new CRDs.\n    Pay special attention to:\n    - Removed / renamed controller flags.\n    - Changes to the ConfigMap key schema.\n    - Webhook API version changes.\n    - Kubernetes version compatibility matrix.\n\n0d. Snapshot current state:\n    ```\n    kubectl -n ingress-nginx get deploy ingress-nginx-controller -o yaml > pre-upgrade-deploy.yaml\n    kubectl -n ingress-nginx get cm ingress-nginx-controller -o yaml > pre-upgrade-cm.yaml\n    kubectl get validatingwebhookconfiguration ingress-nginx-admission -o yaml > pre-upgrade-webhook.yaml\n    kubectl -n demo get ingress -o yaml > pre-upgrade-ingresses.yaml\n    ```\n\n### Step 1 – Remediate D4 (availability during upgrade)\nScale to 2 replicas so rolling update has an active pod throughout:\n```\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx scale deploy ingress-nginx-controller --replicas=2\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\n```\n\n### Step 2 – Apply the new manifest\nApply the new upstream manifest (which carries the new image and updated RBAC):\n```\nkubectl apply -f ingress-nginx-vX.Y.Z.yaml\n```\nThis will update: Deployment, RBAC, Services, ValidatingWebhookConfiguration.\n\n### Step 3 – Patch the Deployment to carry forward non-standard config and fix defects\nAfter applying the base manifest, apply the following targeted patches:\n\n**3a – Fix D1: remove stale --watch-ingress-without-class=true arg**\nUse `kubectl edit` or a strategic-merge-patch to ensure only ONE occurrence of\n`--watch-ingress-without-class=false` remains in `.spec.template.spec.containers[0].args`.\n\n**3b – Fix D2: restore terminationGracePeriodSeconds**\n```\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx patch deploy ingress-nginx-controller \\\n  --type=json \\\n  -p='[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/terminationGracePeriodSeconds\",\"value\":300}]'\n```\n\n**3c – Retain --publish-status-address if still needed**\nIf the cluster still requires `--publish-status-address=localhost` (kind dev cluster),\nadd it back to the args after the new manifest apply strips it or changes it.\nFor a production cluster, omit this flag.\n\n**3d – Retain tolerations for control-plane scheduling if needed**\nThe current Deployment tolerates `node-role.kubernetes.io/master:NoSchedule` and\n`node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane:NoSchedule`.  Confirm the new manifest preserves\nthese tolerations if the controller must run on control-plane nodes.\n\n### Step 4 – Wait for rollout to complete\n```\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --timeout=5m\n```\n\n### Step 5 – Create missing demo-app Service and Ingress\nThe demo-app in namespace `demo` has no Service or Ingress.  These must be created to\nexpose traffic through the upgraded controller:\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: demo-app\n  namespace: demo\nspec:\n  selector:\n    app: demo-app\n  ports:\n  - port: 80\n    targetPort: 5678\n---\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Ingress\nmetadata:\n  name: demo-app\n  namespace: demo\n  annotations:\n    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target: /\nspec:\n  ingressClassName: nginx\n  rules:\n  - host: demo.example.com\n    http:\n      paths:\n      - path: /\n        pathType: Prefix\n        backend:\n          service:\n            name: demo-app\n            port:\n              number: 80\n```\nAdjust the hostname and any annotations to match environment requirements.\n\n### Step 6 – Post-upgrade verification\n```\n# Controller pod is running the new image\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx get pods -o wide\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx get deploy ingress-nginx-controller \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}'\n\n# No duplicate args\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx get deploy ingress-nginx-controller \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].args}' | tr ',' '\\n' \\\n  | grep watch-ingress-without-class\n\n# terminationGracePeriodSeconds is 300\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx get deploy ingress-nginx-controller \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.terminationGracePeriodSeconds}'\n\n# Webhook is healthy\nkubectl get validatingwebhookconfiguration ingress-nginx-admission -o yaml | grep failurePolicy\n\n# Ingress resources report an address\nkubectl -n demo get ingress\n\n# End-to-end connectivity (adjust host/port)\ncurl -H 'Host: demo.example.com' http://localhost/\n```\n\n### Step 7 – Scale back to 1 replica (if desired)\n```\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx scale deploy ingress-nginx-controller --replicas=1\n```\n\n### Step 8 – Post-upgrade smoke test + rollback gate\nMonitor controller logs for 10 minutes:\n```\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx logs -f deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\n```\nIf any critical errors are observed, roll back:\n```\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout undo deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Risk Register\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|------------|\n| Rolling update downtime (1 replica, maxUnavailable=1) | High | Step 1: scale to 2 before upgrade |\n| Webhook outage blocks Ingress changes during pod churn | Medium | Ensure new pod Ready before old is removed (fixed by Step 1) |\n| Duplicate --watch-ingress-without-class causes log noise or future confusion | Low | Fix in Step 3a |\n| preStop hook silently ignored (terminationGracePeriodSeconds=0) | High | Fix in Step 3b |\n| Breaking flag changes in new release | Variable | Step 0c: read changelog before applying |\n| Demo-app unreachable (no Service/Ingress) | Confirmed absent | Step 5: create Service + Ingress |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Procedure\n```\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout undo deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\n```\nThis restores the previous ReplicaSet (revision 2, image v1.14.1) in a rolling fashion.\nPre-upgrade manifests saved in Step 0d can be re-applied if the Deployment spec itself\nwas changed in ways that `rollout undo` does not cover.\nPLANEOF\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap in demo namespace with plan.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2621,"cache_read_input_tokens":37929,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2621},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"669e364a-6af2-4d89-b7ef-d24af1caf6a6","uuid":"4893fb6c-03d4-4566-b7d0-374d7bcbfdef","request_id":"req_011CcL9VqyoJ4qrufB3Mf7n1"}
